HEADWORD: Free-milling
<hw>Free"-mill`ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Yielding free
gold or silver; -- said of certain ores which can be reduced by crushing
and amalgamation, without roasting or other chemical treatment.</def>
<rj><au>Raymond.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

